11: You can see that the two reviewers have read your manuscript and are pleased with your revisions.  They have essentially “signed off” on the paper.  (I will say more about what I’d like you to do about their brief remarks.). I independently read the paper and agree with the reviewers.  I think that you have done a very good job at responding to the comments of the reviewers and I think that the paper as a result is considerably stronger.
12: RESPONSE: Thank you very much for your thoughtful handling of our manuscript and for your careful, independent reading of the revision. We are grateful for the whole review team’s constructive engagement throughout this process. We believe that the review team’s feedback has meaningfully improved our paper, and we appreciate the opportunity to address the remaining points in our latest revision.
